            "introduction": {
              "introduction": "　An attacker who fights with custom-built drones and enhances allied armored units. \n\n　Surprisingly, John Mason has a doctorate degree in engineering which is unusual for a mercenary. He acquired his degree so quickly that he was even offered a job as professor. He isn't lying when he calls himself an intelligent mercenary.\n　John roams the battlefield alone, equipped with the cutting edge gear he invented. Probably because he learned from an experienced veteran that money often causes conflict among mercenaries, he insists on keeping a one-man office.\n　However, his office has never made profit ever since its establishment, because he only chooses the most expensive materials to build his own gear. "
            },
